CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 7, 1939, pg. 16, reads: "THE RELENTLESS RENS OF '39 - ALREADY SOARING TO NEW RECORDS: Left to right: Tarzan Cooper, John Isaacs, Eyre Saitch, "Fats" Jenkins, Zack Clayton, Puggy Bell, "Pop" Gates and "Wee Willie" Smith. Here you have the fast-moving, sure-shooting Rennaisance [Renaissance] floor five of 1938-39.  After vanquishing the Westinghouse Airbrakes team Friday night in Homestead gym, they appear to be going places this season. - Photo by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Renaissance "Rens" basketball team members, Tarzan Cooper, John Isaacs, Eyre Saitch, "Fats" Jenkins, Zack Clayton, Puggy Bell, "Pop" Gates, and "Wee Willie" Smith, in gymnasium with basketball hoop in background
